parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning computer chip can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle fails to start intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical short in the wiring harness can cause the dashboard lights and indicators to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Dashboard lights and indicators do not work in damp or cold weather
electrical short in the wiring harness under the dash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the analog instrument panel can cause the driver to lose access to critical information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Analog instrument panel fails to display information
dealer recommends replacement of the analog cluster.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss, and poses a risk to the driver and occupants.
symptoms: potentially caused by a faulty catalytic converter or electrical system
resulting in a total loss of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause a loss of braking power, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to pull to one side when braking, reducing braking effectiveness and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the vehicle experiences reduced braking effectiveness
the ABS system fails to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latch can cause the seat belt to unlock or become stuck, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The seat belt unlocks by itself while the vehicle is in motion or stationary
the seat belt becomes stuck and cannot be unlatched
the seat belt over-tightens and becomes difficult to remove.
